What Does Bayon Temple Represent? The Face-Filled Mystery of ...|https://journeycambodia.com/what-does-bayon-temple-represent/|Jayavarman VII built this amazing place. The stone faces are really big – as tall as a giraffe! Some faces smile, others look serious. All of them seem to follow you with their eyes. What does Bayon Temple represent? It shows the king’s power and his Buddhist faith. You’ll want to bring your camera when you visit.  ...    Bayon Temple has 216 huge faces carved in stone. They’re about 13 feet tall! Four faces sit on each tower, looking north, south, east, and west. Many people feel like the eyes follow them around. These faces stand for a Buddhist being named Avalokitesvara. He helps people who are sad or in trouble. What does Bayon  ...    Hindu ways. All those faces stand for Avalokitesvara, who Buddhists believe helps anyone who needs it. The faces look at all four directions because they want to see everyone. This fits with Buddhist teaching that we  ...    What do the stone faces mean? The faces show Avalokitesvara, a Buddhist helper figure. Many people think they also look like
The Bayon – The Temple of Faces | theraulaz.ch|https://theraulaz.ch/en/travel/cambodia/siem-reap/the-bayon/|These faces are believed to represent King Jayavarman VII himself, or a fusion of the king and the bodhisattva Avalokiteshvara.  ...    earlier Hindu temples, the Bayon is a Mahayana Buddhist sanctuary, dedicated to Lokeshvara, the bodhisattva of  ...    These smiling faces, with half-closed eyes, embody transcendent serenity. Their meaning remains debated: - Expression of the king’s benevolent watchfulness over the cardinal directions. - Idealized portrait of Jayavarman VII, deified through the bodhisattva. - Representations of Lokeshvara, embodiment of universal compassion.  ...    ## Religious Symbolism  The Bayon expresses a Buddhist cosmology centered on the king: - The faces’ orientation implies a divine presence in all directions, an omniscient and benevolent power. - The temple embodies a mandala of a balanced universe, with the king at its center. - The
